  "prompt": "Why there is no true love in this world?",
  "response": "The concept of true love is subjective and can vary greatly from person to person. While some may feel that true love is rare or difficult to find, others may believe that it exists and can be experienced. The perception of true love can be influenced by personal experiences, cultural norms, societal expectations, and individual beliefs.\n\nIt's important to consider that love, in its many forms\u2014romantic, familial, platonic\u2014can be complex and multifaceted. True love often requires mutual respect, understanding, communication, and effort from both parties involved. It may not always be perfect or free from challenges, but many people do experience deep, meaningful connections that they consider to be true love.\n\nIf you feel that true love is lacking in your life or in the world, it might be helpful to reflect on your own expectations and experiences, and consider ways to foster love and connection in your relationships. Building meaningful connections often takes time, effort, and vulnerability.\n\nUltimately, the existence of true love is a deeply personal belief and experience, and while it may seem elusive to some, others find it in various forms and relationships throughout their lives.",
